## Constraints

- System settings: key-value, typed schema validation
- Audit log view: cursor pagination (büyük tablo), filter by user/action/date/entity
- Audit log export: CSV (Excel compatible) + JSON (forensic)
- Audit chain verify: button triggers verification, shows broken sequence if any
- Consent version: draft → publish transition. Publish forces all users to re-accept.
- Data retention: notifications 90d (default, configurable), audit infinite (compliance)
- System settings cache: Redis 5 dk

## Done Definition

- [ ] System settings CRUD + validation
- [ ] Audit log list with filters (user, action, entity, date range, outcome)
- [ ] Audit log detail: full context + chain neighborhood visualization
- [ ] Audit export: CSV + JSON (rate-limited 5/hour)
- [ ] Audit chain verify: button → verification result display
- [ ] Consent version publish: draft → active, users forced re-accept
- [ ] Admin dashboard: active user count, process count, overdue task count
- [ ] Data retention cron test
- [ ] AUDIT_LOG_VIEW, SYSTEM_SETTINGS_EDIT, CONSENT_VERSION_EDIT permission enforcement

## Explicit Don'ts

- User impersonation (post-MVP — security concern)
- System-wide announcement broadcast (post-MVP)
- Audit log manual edit (tamper resistance — yasak)
- Auto-repair broken chain (incident response, not automated)
- Multi-tenant admin panel (single-tenant MVP)

## Related ADRs

- ADR-0026: Audit log no auto-repair policy
- ADR-0027: Consent re-accept on publish (vs gradual)

